Paper: hep-th/0007132

Date: 2000-07-17

Title: Supercriticality and Transmission Resonances in the Dirac equation

Authors: N Dombey, P Kennedy and A Calogeracos

Comments: Submitted to Physical Review Letters

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 85 (2000) 1787-1790

It is shown that a Dirac particle of mass $m$ and arbitrarily small momentumwill tunnel without reflection through a potential barrier $V=U_c(x)$ of finiterange provided that the potential well $V=-U_c(x)$ supports a bound state ofenergy $E=-m.$ This is called a supercritical potential well.